pageContext.claim: “Obamacare is a disaster. It's too expensive, not working.”
pageContext.analysis: Credible estimates suggest the health-care law boosted the number of people with health insurance by 20 million. The Congressional Budget Office said that the individual market would be stable in most markets at least for the next ten years under the Affordable Care Act. For people who qualify for subsidies to help pay for insurance on the Obamacare exchanges -- roughly three-quarters of participants -- most options are rather affordable. Trump often claims he has made the program better, but he's has tried to undermine it.
